qas.question: The uneasy alliance between whom eventually won rebels the victory?
The fight against Huerta formally ended on which date?
In which city did Obregon sign a number of treaties?
Who made a triumphant entry into Mexico City on August 20, 1914?

context: The uneasy alliance of <a0_0>Carranza, Obregón, Villa, and Zapata<a0_0/> eventually led the rebels to victory. The fight against Huerta formally ended on <a1_0>August 15, 1914<a1_0/>, when Álvaro Obregón signed a number of treaties in <a2_0>Teoloyucan<a2_0/> in which the last of Huerta's forces surrendered to him and recognized the constitutional government. On August 20, 1914, <a3_0>Carranza<a3_0/> made a triumphal entry into Mexico City. Carranza (supported by Obregón) was now the strongest candidate to fill the power vacuum and set himself up as head of the new government. This government successfully printed money, passed laws, etc.
